# DentistasMiami.com - Project Rules

## Project Overview
Building a professional Spanish-language dental directory for Miami using Next.js 15, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- MDX for content
- Zod for validation
- Google Places API for dentist data

## Code Style & Standards

### TypeScript
- Use TypeScript for all files (.ts, .tsx)
- Enable strict mode
- Never use 'any' - use 'unknown' if type is truly unknown

### React/Next.js
- Use Server Components by default
- Only add 'use client' when necessary
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components

### Security
- Validate all user input with Zod schemas
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Never expose API keys to client

### Spanish Language
- All user-facing content in Spanish
- Use natural, conversational tone

## When Helping Me Code
1. Always explain what the code does
2. Point out security considerations
3. Ensure TypeScript types are correct